  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "In hibernate region, the `missing_tick` is used for recording the raft tick count. If the peer's state becomes chaotic, the missing ticks will be called for `missing_tick` times. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/tikv/tikv/blob/4a75902f266fbbc064f0c19a2a681cfe66511bc3/components/raftstore/src/store/fsm/peer.rs#L962-L971\r\n\r\nBy default, if this peer is hibernated, the `missing_tick` should be 9.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/tikv/tikv/blob/4a75902f266fbbc064f0c19a2a681cfe66511bc3/components/raftstore/src/store/fsm/peer.rs#L1114-L1117\r\nIn `reset_raft_tick` functions, the `missing_tick` is reset to zero, which may lead to a slow leader election when the old leader is dead, namely, more round of election timeout.\r\n\r\nWhen an old leader A is dead, follower B may become chaotic quicker than follower C.\r\nThen follower B will tick for `missing_tick` times immediately and may send vote msg to follower C.\r\n\r\nIf follower C receives the vote msg before running `missing_tick`. It will refuse this vote because of the code in raft-rs.\r\nhttps://github.com/tikv/raft-rs/blob/91d883287317e7a7ca18acbab6b405d4168b3b73/src/raft.rs#L1109-L1137\r\n\r\nIf so, both two peers need to wait for the next election timeout to choose a new leader.\r\n",
